  title: 中秋直宿玉堂
  author: 申從濩
  language: lzh
  text: 細把瓊杯待玉蟾夜寒風露滿踈簾生憎屋角梧桐樹遮斷淸光不到簷
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 中秋直宿玉堂
  author: 申從濩
  language: lzh
  text: 細把瓊杯待玉蟾。夜寒風露滿踈簾。生憎屋角梧桐樹。遮斷淸光不到簷。
korean:
  title: 중추 직숙 옥당
  author: 신종호
  language: kor
  text: |-
    가늘게 옥잔 잡아 달을 기다리노라니
    차가운 밤 성긴 주렴 바람 이슬 가득
    미울손 추녀 끝 저 오동나무
    맑은 빛 가로막아 처마 안 못 비추네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0260&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Autumn Equinox Night Watch in the Jade Hall
  author: Shin Jong-ho
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I cradle the jade cup delicately, waiting for the moon.
    The cold night wind carries dew through the gossamer curtain.
    How I resent that parasol tree at the roof's edge—
    It steals away the pure light, leaving the eaves in shadow.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'Jade Hall' (옥당/玉堂) refers to the Hall of Worthies, an elite administrative office, suggesting the poet is on official night duty.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'jade cup' and 'moon' carry traditional associations with Mid-Autumn Festival celebration and scholarly contemplation.
  - key: ''
    value: The parasol tree (오동나무/梧桐) is a classical image of melancholy and separation in East Asian poetry.
